From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Disable process jobs in Cabal library on Windows

The Cabal library bundled with GHC 9.2.8 enables process jobs on Windows 8+
via Distribution.Compat.Process.enableProcessJobs. This causes "Invalid argument"
errors when building with Hadrian on Azure DevOps, which already runs builds
inside a job object.

This patch disables process jobs in Cabal's process wrappers to avoid
nested job object conflicts.

See also: disable-process-job-objects-windows.patch (for GHC's SysTools)

diff --git a/libraries/Cabal/Cabal/src/Distribution/Compat/Process.hs b/libraries/Cabal/Cabal/src/Distribution/Compat/Process.hs
--- a/libraries/Cabal/Cabal/src/Distribution/Compat/Process.hs
+++ b/libraries/Cabal/Cabal/src/Distribution/Compat/Process.hs
@@ -53,9 +53,12 @@ isWindows8OrLater = unsafePerformIO $ do
 -- automatically inherits the job. But at it also tries to assign a
 -- new job J2 to C since it doesn't have access J1. This fails on
 -- Windows 7 or before.
+--
+-- CONDA-FORGE: Disabled unconditionally to avoid conflicts with Azure DevOps
+-- job objects which cause "builderMainLoop: invalid argument" errors.
 enableProcessJobs :: CreateProcess -> CreateProcess
-#if defined(mingw32_HOST_OS) && MIN_VERSION_process(1,6,9)
-enableProcessJobs cp = cp {Process.use_process_jobs = isWindows8OrLater}
+#if 0
+enableProcessJobs cp = cp {Process.use_process_jobs = False}
 #else
 enableProcessJobs cp = cp
 #endif
